      I agree with you there, but I think your standards are too unclear for me to support them.  I think it is good to have our officials campaign while they are still serving, and that there should be clearer descriptions of their responsibilities to their office.  I believe that description would be more effective than dropping their salary, because it would invite public criticism when they break it.<br/><br/>If someone really is neglecting their responsibilities, they should be able to have someone else act as proxy.  That should alleviate part of the problem.

                  
    </td>
  </tr>

</table>



    
    <ul class="noimage">
      <li>
        <a class="iconLink" href="javascript:ajaxLink('PostComment_3189', '/akira/postComment.do?dbid=2247&topicID=3189&mode=add-comment-show')"><img alt="Add New" class="iconLink" src="/images/iconshock/add_16.gif" border="0">&nbsp;Post New Comment</a>

        <div id="PostComment_3189"></div>
      </li>
    </ul>      
    


  </div>

  

  








  
    






